message: To succeed, always aim to combine one natural ingredient with one artificial ingredient; this often yields a 30-value item. Avoid combining more than two ingredients at once, as it consistently leads to negative 'overcomplicated' items. The optimal path to 100 value is: combine (natural+artificial) to get 30, then use 'scissors' on that item to get 80, and finally use 'frame' on the 80-value item to reach 100. The 'frame' tool is best used as the *very last* step. Using 'scissors' on a 0-value item can sometimes raise it to 50, then 'frame' can raise it to 70, but this is usually not the path to 100. Be careful not to 'over-process' items with tools, as repeated applications or incorrect sequences can ruin them.
